HEADWORD: Economizer
<hw>E*con"o*mi`zer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, economizes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically: <fld>(Steam Boilers)</fld> An
arrangement of pipes for heating feed water by waste heat in the gases
passing to the chimney.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>economy</ent>⟦br⟧
